- System resource usage (CPU and memory) is crucial for understanding query performance in the context of overall system load; 
- The ranking of queries by execution time helps identify bottlenecks or areas for optimization;
- The inclusion of both query-specific metrics (e.g., join time, sort time) and system-wide metrics (e.g., CPU usage, memory usage) provides a holistic view of database performance.

- In this context, a "successfully optimized" query refers to a query with an optimization status of 'completed';
- The term "viewed" refers to an access type of 'view';
- The IP address '192.168.1.1' is used to restrict the access origin.

